        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>I realized that an N.C. State student taught me more in one short cab ride than most of the professors I’ve had at Duke have taught me in a semester.</p>
<br>
<p>What I learned tonight—about stereotypes, misconceptions, world events and human nature—Duke’s professors will never teach me. And though they might try, they will never get through to me like that young man who has been wondering for four months if his family, thousands of miles away, is all right.</p>
<p>I sincerely hope that they are.</p>
<em>Jason Greenwald is a Trinity sophomore. He is a sports reporter for The Chronicle.</em>

